- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithms for counting perfect matchings.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper examines the complexity of counting perfect matchings in different classes of graphs.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the paper uses the switch Markov chain, which is a tool commonly used in game theory.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with graph structures and their properties, which can be relevant to social and information networks.
